IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: HOSPICE IN HOME CARE OF TERMINALLY ILL PATIENTS AND COMPREHENSIVE GUIDANCE AND SUPPORT FOR PATIENTS AND THEIR FAMILIES.
IRS990.MissionDescription: TO IMPROVE THE QUALITY OF LIFE FOR PATIENTS AND FAMILIES AND BE THE COMPASSIONATE GUIDE FOR END-OF-LIFE CARE IN OUR COMMUNITY.
IRS990.Description: THE COMMUNITY HOSPICE OF NORTHEAST FLORIDA PROVIDED MEDICAL AND PALLIATIVE CARE, PSYCHOLOGICAL, PHYSICAL AND SPIRITUAL SERVICES TO TERMINALLY ILL PATIENTS AND THEIR FAMILIES REGARDLESS OF THEIR ABILITY TO PAY. EDUCATION AND TRAINING IS PROVIDED TO EXPAND AND ENHANCE KNOWLEDGE OF DEATH AND DYING CARE TO PATIENTS, FAMILY MEMBERS AND THE COMMUNITY. DURING THE FISCAL YEAR ENDED SEPTEMBER 30, 2010, 6,382 PATIENTS AND THEIR FAMILIES WERE SERVED TOTALING 335,600 DAYS OF CARE. NUMEROUS COMMUNITY EVENTS WERE HOSTED TO ALLOW ALL MEMBERS OF THE 5 COUNTY AREA THE OPPORTUNITY TO GET A BETTER UNDERSTANDING OF HOSPICE AND PALLIATIVE CARE. DURING THE YEAR, THE HOSPICE BEGAN A PALLIATIVE CARE PROGRAM WITHIN LOCAL HOSPITALS.

Form990ScheduleCPartIV.Explanation: THE ORGANIZATION INCURRED EXPENSES LOBBYING FOR A LEGISLATIVE AMENDMENT THAT WOULD POTENTIALLY ALLOW FLORIDA HOSPICES TO PRACTICE PALLIATIVE CARE UNDER EXISTING FLORIDA HOSPICE LICENSES. LOBBYING WAS PERFORMED VIA PERSONAL VISITS TO STATE SENATORS.

Form990ScheduleIPartIV.Identifier: Procedure for Monitoring Grants in the U.S.:
Form990ScheduleIPartIV.Explanation: Schedule I, Part I, Line 2: THE ORGANIZATION FUNDS A FELLOWSHIP THROUGH THE MAYO CLINIC THAT HELPS SUBSIDIZES A FELLOW TO PERFORM ROUNDS AT THE HOSPICE'S INPATIENT FACILITY. THE FELLOW ALSO HANDLES THE INTERDISCIPLINARY TEAM MEETING EACH WEEK, AND IS OVERSEEN BY THE HOSPICE'S MEDICAL STAFF WHEN ON SITE. WHILE THE FUNDS ARE USED TO SUBSIDIZE A FELLOW'S SALARY AND BENEFITS, THE FELLOWSHIP IS CONSIDERED A GRANT TO THE MAYO CLINIC FOR USE IN THIS ESTABLISHED PROGRAM, AS THERE IS NO DIRECT RELATIONSHIP BETWEEN THE GRANT AND THE SERVICE BY A FELLOW AT THE HOSPICE. ALL SIGNIFICANT DEVIATIONS IN THE USE OF THE GRANT FROM THE PURPOSE DESCIRBED ABOVE MUST BE APPROVED BY THE ORGANIZATION. THE FELLOWSHIP PROGRAM IS A WELL-ESTABLISHED PROGRAM WITHIN THE MAYO CLINIC, AND UPDATES AND REPORTS ON THE USE OF FUNDS IS READILY AVAILABLE FOR THE ORGANIZATION TO OBTAIN.

Form990ScheduleLPartIV.Relationship: FAMILY RELATIONSHIP WITH KEY EMPLOYEE JOHN MCILVAINE

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 11
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE RETURN WAS PREPARED BY AN INDEPENDENT ACCOUNTANT WITH ASSISTANCE AND OVERSIGHT BY MANAGEMENT. UPON COMPLETION, THE RETURN WAS REVIEWED IN ITS ENTIRETY BY THE BUDGET FINANCE COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD, FOLLOWED BY A PRESENTATION TO THE FULL BOARD FOR APPROVAL. FOLLOWING APPROVAL, THE RETURN WAS FILED WITH THE IRS.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 12c
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: MEMBERS OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS ARE REQUIRED ANNUALLY TO COMPLETE AND SIGN A CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY IDENTIFYING RELATIONSHIPS THAT MAY GIVE RISE TO CONFLICT. OFFICERS AND KEY MANAGEMENT PERSONNEL ALSO COMPLETE A SURVEY REGARDING POTENTIAL BUSINESS RELATIONSHIPS WITH OTHER OFFICERS, DIRECTORS, AND KEY PERSONNEL.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 15
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: USING CURRENT JOB DESCRIPTIONS FOR THE EXECUTIVE POSITIONS, COMPETITIVE COMPENSATION DATA IS COLLECTED FROM PUBLISHED SALARY SURVEYS, THE FORM 990 OF SIMILAR HOSPICES, AND THROUGH DATA SUPPLIED BY EXTERNAL COMPENSATION CONSULTANTS. THIS INFORMATION IS ORGANIZED AND PRESENTED TO THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD BY THE DIRECTOR OF HUMAN RESOURCES. THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE IN TURN DETERMINES AND APPROVES INDIVIDUAL SALARY ADJUSTMENTS IT BELIEVES ARE WARRANTED. THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE REVIEWS COMPENSATION FOR THE CEO, COO, CFO, DEPUTY CFO, CMO, CNO, VP OF WORKFORCE DEVELOPMENT, VP OF MARKETING DEVELOPMENT, VP OF MARKETING & COMMUNICATIONS, VP OF BUSINESS DEVELOPMENT, AND THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR OF THE RELATED FOUNDATION.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, line 18
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: PHOTOCOPIES OF THE FORM 990 ARE AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST AT THE ORGANIZATION'S ADMINISTRATIVE OFFICE. IN ADDITION, RECENT FILINGS OF THE FORM 990 ARE AVAILABLE ONLINE AT WWW.GUIDESTAR.ORG.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, line 19
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE ORGANIZATION WILL PROVIDE ANY GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICIES, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS UPON REQUEST. THIS CAN BE DONE IN PERSON, BY PHONE, VIA OUR WEBSITE OR ON WWW.GUIDESTAR.COM. THE ORGANIZATION PUBLISHES A COMMUNITY REPORT IN THE LOCAL SUNDAY NEWSPAPER THAT PROVIDES SUMMARY INFORMATION OF THE PREVIOUS YEAR.
